BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:avistavulcao-azores-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260802
SUMMARY:Deadline: AVISTAVULCÃO: Azores Artist Residency 2027 (Faial\, Port
 ugal)
DESCRIPTION:AVISTAVULCÃO opens a call for a one-month artist-in-residence 
 programme focused on research and creation\, taking place in March 2027 an
 d intended for an artist or artistic duo. Located on the island of Faial n
 ear the Capelinhos Volcano (Azores\, Portugal)\, the residency offers imme
 rsion in a territory shaped by geology\, insularity\, and the interplay be
 tween nature and human presence\, with the Azores treated as living materi
 al for creation. Artists are invited to develop projects engaging with lan
 dscape\, memory\, local history\, and the contemporary challenges facing p
 eripheral regions\; suggested starting points include geological time\, tr
 ansformation\, resilience\, isolation\, mobility\, and the relationships b
 etween communities and the environment. Context-sensitive proposals that p
 rioritise observation\, listening and a relationship with the place are va
 lued. Residents meet local stakeholders and share moments with the communi
 ty\, culminating in a public presentation of the process or results. SUPPO
 RT (in-person mobility): EUR 1\,350 allowance per resident\, travel allowa
 nce of EUR 400 to 800\, green mobility top-up of EUR 400\, visa top-up of 
 EUR 120 per resident\, outermost regions top-up of EUR 175 per resident\, 
 family top-up of EUR 200 per child\, and accessibility support. ELIGIBILIT
 Y: individual artists and duos (cross-disciplinary welcome) from countries
  eligible for the Creative Europe programme. DEADLINE: 1 August 2026.\n\nO
 rganisation: AVISTAVULCÃO / Barca 13\nLocation: Faial Island\, Azores\, P
 ortugal (near the Capelinhos Volcano). Open to artists from countries elig
 ible for the Creative Europe programme.\nAward: EUR 1\,350 allowance per r
 esident for the month\, plus travel allowance (EUR 400 to 800)\, green mob
 ility top-up (EUR 400)\, visa top-up (EUR 120/resident)\, outermost region
 s and overseas territories top-up (EUR 175/resident)\, family top-up (EUR 
 200 per child/resident)\, and accessibility support. No application fee.\n
 Duration: One month\, March 2027\n\nMore: https://www.barca13.pt/en/avista
 vulcao/agora/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.barca13.pt/en/avistavulcao/agora/?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Faial Island\, Azores\, Portugal (near the Capelinhos Volcano). Op
 en to artists from countries eligible for the Creative Europe programme.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlin-senate-arbeitsstipendium-bildende-kunst-2027@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlin Senate: Arbeitsstipendium Bildende Kunst 2027 (Ber
 lin residents only)
DESCRIPTION:The Berlin Senate's work stipends for visual artists fund 8 or 
 12 months of artistic work during 2027 at EUR 2\,000 per month. The progra
 m explicitly covers digital art and media art\, sound art\, artistic film 
 and video (shown in a visual-arts exhibition context) and installation\, a
 longside classical visual-arts disciplines. ELIGIBILITY: professional visu
 al artists who live\, work and are registered in Berlin\; not open to appl
 icants based elsewhere. The application window runs 6 July to 2 September 
 2026\, 11:00 CEST\, via the Senate's online portal.\n\nOrganisation: Berli
 n Senate Department for Culture and Social Cohesion\nLocation: Berlin\, Ge
 rmany. BERLIN RESIDENTS ONLY: applicants must live\, work and be officiall
 y registered in Berlin.\nAward: EUR 16\,000 (8 months) or EUR 24\,000 (12 
 months)\, paid as EUR 2\,000 per month. No application fee.\nDuration: 8 o
 r 12 months during 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/en/fundi
 ng/funding-programmes/visual-arts/artikel.230092.en.php?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/en/funding/funding-programmes/visual-a
 rts/artikel.230092.en.php?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium
 =referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany. BERLIN RESIDENTS ONLY: applicants must live\, wo
 rk and be officially registered in Berlin.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prisma-art-prize-20th-edition-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260910
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260911
SUMMARY:Deadline: Prisma Art Prize 20th Edition
DESCRIPTION:The Prisma Art Prize is an international award for painting and
  two-dimensional artistic research based in Rome. The 20th edition selects
  emerging and established artists working in painting\, drawing\, illustra
 tion\, printmaking\, and traditional mixed media for a group exhibition at
  Palazzo Merulana\, opening November 5\, 2026. Winners share an annual cas
 h fund of EUR 2\,000 distributed across quarterly calls and receive inclus
 ion in the collective catalogue plus artist interviews. Additional opportu
 nities include solo exhibition prizes and fully funded placements at partn
 er art residencies. The prize is open internationally to all living artist
 s regardless of age\, gender\, nationality\, or educational background. Th
 e submission deadline for this edition is September 10\, 2026.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Prisma Art Prize\nLocation: Rome\, Italy\nAward: EUR 2\,000 annual c
 ash fund distributed across quarterly winners\, plus group exhibition at P
 alazzo Merulana\, inclusion in the collective catalogue\, artist interview
 s\, and eligibility for solo show prizes (Isorrophia Gallery\, Pallavicini
 -Dettori) and partner art residencies (Dar Meso\, Casacon\, Osservatorioma
 ree) EUR 34 entry fee for 1 to 3 artworks\, plus EUR 5 for each additional
  artwork up to a maximum of 8\nDuration: Group exhibition runs November 5 
 to 8\, 2026\n\nMore: https://www.prismaartprize.com/?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.prismaartprize.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Rome\, Italy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cmrfe-multispecies-residency-autumn-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: Artist Residency Autumn 2026 (Centre for Multispecies Rel
 ations and Future Ecologies\, Palermo)
DESCRIPTION:The Centre for Multispecies Relations and Future Ecologies invi
 tes applications from two artists for a 62-day residency (12 October - 12 
 December 2026) at its site in the Altarello di Baida district of Palermo\,
  Sicily. The residency is structured around a 1\,500 sqm garden at the thr
 eshold between the city's urban expansion and the historic rural landscape
  of the surrounding hills\; the site\, degraded through previous use (soil
  compaction and significant biodiversity loss)\, functions as both studio 
 and subject\, and artists participate in an ongoing process of ecological 
 transformation\, producing interventions that emerge from extended observa
 tion and fieldwork. Applications are welcome across all mediums and discip
 lines (installation\, sound\, performance\, video\, food art\, participato
 ry practice\, and beyond)\; research-based and interdisciplinary practices
  are especially encouraged. The Centre works at the intersection of art\, 
 science\, and (agro)ecological practices\, with a focus on multispecies co
 existence and climate change in the Mediterranean\, and has been based in 
 Palermo since 2021. PROGRAMME: five phases (orientation with small trips a
 nd gatherings\; observation with independent fieldwork and consultations w
 ith artists\, curators\, scientists\, and anthropologists\; proposal and e
 cological feasibility developed with mentors\; creation\; and public resti
 tution with an open event\, a workshop\, and a public discussion). Each ar
 tist develops an independent site-specific intervention\; the two resident
 s share the site\, living space\, and process\, with exchange encouraged b
 ut not prescribed. Artist duos and artists who want to collaborate are enc
 ouraged to apply (you can apply as an individual for one position\, as a d
 uo for both\, or as two artists collaborating for two positions). Mentorsh
 ip by co-founders/artistic directors Fabio Aranzulla and Luca Cinquemani (
 weekly site visits\, studio discussions\, work-in-progress presentations)\
 ; logistics managed by Francesca Farris. WHO: artists whose work engages w
 ith ecology\, multispecies relations\, or the more-than-human\, who can mo
 ve between observation and making and are interested in dialogue with scie
 ntists\, land workers\, and local communities. Priority is given to artist
 s from working-class and less-privileged backgrounds\, those who self-iden
 tify as part of marginalised communities\, and candidates reflecting diver
 sity in gender\, age\, geographical background\, and ability\; green trave
 l is prioritised as a condition of participation where feasible. Applicant
 s should be open to living and working in a neighbourhood on the margins o
 f Palermo's periphery. Funded by Culture Moves Europe (Creative Europe pro
 gramme of the European Union). APPLICATION: first phase via the online for
 m (opened 10 June)\; shortlisted artists contacted before the end of July\
 ; second phase is video calls with shortlisted candidates\; applications a
 ccepted in English and Italian. Contact: contact.cmrfe@gmail.com. Deadline
  5 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Centre for Multispecies Relations and Futur
 e Ecologies\nLocation: Altarello di Baida district\, Palermo\, Sicily\, It
 aly. On-site 62-day residency\, 12 October - 12 December 2026. Open to all
  nationalities\, but applicants must be officially residing in a Creative 
 Europe country (excluding Italy).\nAward: Total allowance of EUR 1\,860 (b
 efore tax) per artist\, plus a travel budget of EUR 400 per artist (for di
 stances under 4\,000 km) with a EUR 400 green-mobility top-up\, plus a pro
 duction budget. Also provided: on-site accommodation in a fully furnished 
 independent house (private bedroom\; shared kitchen\, living room\, two ba
 throoms\; outdoor studio space 100m from the working site)\, access to rec
 ycled/salvaged materials through the Centre's partnerships\, a bicycle per
  resident\, and a final public event.\nDuration: 62-day residency\, 12 Oct
 ober - 12 December 2026\, structured in five phases (orientation\, observa
 tion/fieldwork\, proposal and ecological feasibility\, creation\, and publ
 ic restitution).\n\nMore: https://tally.so/r/81r5Mz?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://tally.so/r/81r5Mz?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
LOCATION:Altarello di Baida district\, Palermo\, Sicily\, Italy. On-site 62
 -day residency\, 12 October - 12 December 2026. Open to all nationalities\
 , but applicants must be officially residing in a Creative Europe country 
 (excluding Italy).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:galerie-tic-open-call-2027-galerie-mladych@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260720
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260721
SUMMARY:Deadline: Open Call 2027: Galerie mladych (Galerie TIC Brno)
DESCRIPTION:Galerie TIC announces an open call for exhibition projects for 
 Galerie mladych (Gallery of Young Artists) for the year 2027. Applicants s
 hould send a completed application form\, a project description with visua
 l documentation\, and an artist's portfolio with CV by midnight on 20 July
  2026 via the online form. THE GALLERY OFFERS: to cover the financial cost
 s of exhibition installation\; an artist/curator fee\; collection and tran
 sport of the exhibition\; and basic PR (photodocumentation included). APPL
 ICATION: the application form\, a short description and visual documentati
 on of the artistic/curatorial project\, and a portfolio with CV. Results w
 ill be published on the gallery's website and social media no later than t
 he end of August 2026. Deadline 20 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Galerie TIC
  Brno\nLocation: Brno\, Czech Republic. Exhibition projects realized at Ga
 lerie mladych during 2027.\nAward: The gallery covers the financial costs 
 of exhibition installation\, an artist/curator fee\, collection and transp
 ort of the exhibition\, and basic PR (photodocumentation included).\nDurat
 ion: Exhibition project for the year 2027.\n\nMore: https://galerie-tic.cz
 /en/open-call-2027-2?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refe
 rral
URL:https://galerie-tic.cz/en/open-call-2027-2?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Brno\, Czech Republic. Exhibition projects realized at Galerie mla
 dych during 2027.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ay-roop-le-milieu-reuse-circus-residency-2026@artificialnouveau.github.
 io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260703
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260704
SUMMARY:Deadline: AY-ROOP / Le Milieu: Reuse - (Re)making for Circus Reside
 ncy 2026 (Rennes Métropole\, France)
DESCRIPTION:AY-ROOP is launching an open call to select three circus artist
 s and/or circus set designers/builders for a 21-day Culture Moves Europe r
 esearch residency at Le Milieu (Saint-Jacques-de-la-Lande\, Rennes Métrop
 ole) from 28 November to 18 December 2026. The residency is a research lab
 oratory on reuse in contemporary circus: how everyday\, locally available 
 materials (paper/cardboard\, plastics\, lightweight metal\, textiles\, rec
 laimed wood\, bicycle parts\, etc.) can be used to create scenographic ele
 ments\, sets\, props and small apparatuses for juggling\, acrobatics and b
 alancing. The core principle is that objects are recreated locally from re
 sources available in each territory rather than transported. AY-ROOP provi
 des an equipped construction workshop\, a rehearsal stage and circus tent\
 , a guide to local reuse-sector contacts\, and a full residency environmen
 t (accommodation\, shared kitchen\, working facilities)\; two mentors (a r
 euse specialist and a performing-arts professional) support the artists. P
 ROFILES: circus artists interested in construction/scenography/DIY making\
 , and builders/set designers working in circus\; individual or group appli
 cations (max 3 people per group)\; emerging or established\, any backgroun
 d. Accessible to artists with disabilities and accessibility needs. Workin
 g language English. No aerial apparatus or rigging: all work is ground-bas
 ed. ELIGIBILITY: aged 18+ (no upper limit)\; legally resident in a Creativ
 e Europe country other than France and DROM-COM\; available for the full r
 esidency. APPLY with a single PDF (1-page bio/CV\, 5-page portfolio or vid
 eo links\, 1-page statement of intent\, proof of residence). DEADLINE: 3 J
 uly 2026. Results announced 13 July 2026. Check the linked call PDF for fu
 ll details.\n\nOrganisation: AY-ROOP\nLocation: Le Milieu\, Saint-Jacques-
 de-la-Lande\, Rennes Métropole\, France. Applicants must legally reside i
 n a Creative Europe country other than France and the French overseas terr
 itories (DROM-COM).\nAward: Funded through Culture Moves Europe: EUR 900 m
 obility allowance per person plus flat-rate travel coverage\; supplements 
 for green mobility\, visa fees\, dependent children under 18\, OCT/OR resi
 dents\, and disability/accessibility needs (including possible full covera
 ge of a sign-language interpreter). On-site single-room accommodation\, lu
 nches at Le Milieu canteen (Tuesday to Friday)\, shared kitchen\, and tech
 nical support provided. No application fee.\nDuration: 21-day residency\, 
 28 November to 18 December 2026.\n\nMore: https://circusdance.fi/ilmoituks
 et/ay-roop-le-milieu-rennes-metropole-france-open-call-for-circus-artists-
 and-set-designers-for-a-residency-focused-on-the-reuse-of-materials-nov-de
 c-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://circusdance.fi/ilmoitukset/ay-roop-le-milieu-rennes-metropole-f
 rance-open-call-for-circus-artists-and-set-designers-for-a-residency-focus
 ed-on-the-reuse-of-materials-nov-dec-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Le Milieu\, Saint-Jacques-de-la-Lande\, Rennes Métropole\, France
 . Applicants must legally reside in a Creative Europe country other than F
 rance and the French overseas territories (DROM-COM).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:genius-loci-weimar-video-mapping-competition-2026@artificialnouveau.git
 hub.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260615
SUMMARY:Deadline: Genius Loci Weimar: Video Mapping Competition 2026 (Democ
 racy and Society)
DESCRIPTION:Genius Loci Weimar is an annual projection-mapping (video mappi
 ng) festival that invites artists to design audiovisual works for the faca
 des of historic Weimar buildings. The 2026 competition theme is Democracy 
 and Society. Entry is at concept stage: submissions are conceptual proposa
 ls\, and professional video-mapping expertise is not required\, as the org
 anisers provide technical support to realise winning concepts. One winner 
 is selected per facade and receives a EUR 7\,000 production budget\; one s
 elected work additionally receives a EUR 3\,000 festival prize. Open to in
 ternational artists working as individuals or in teams. Winners are announ
 ced around 6 July 2026 and the festival runs 11-13 September 2026. Applica
 tion deadline: 14 June 2026\, 23:59 CET. Register and submit via the offic
 ial competition page.\n\nOrganisation: Genius Loci Weimar\nLocation: Weima
 r\, Germany. Open to international artists\; winning works are projected o
 nto historic facades during the festival.\nAward: EUR 7\,000 production bu
 dget per winning facade (one winner selected per building) plus a EUR 3\,0
 00 festival prize for one selected work. No application fee.\nDuration: Fe
 stival 11-13 September 2026\; deliverable is a roughly 5-minute projection
 -mapping work for a facade.\n\nMore: https://www.genius-loci-weimar.org/en
 /competition-en.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refe
 rral
URL:https://www.genius-loci-weimar.org/en/competition-en.html?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Weimar\, Germany. Open to international artists\; winning works ar
 e projected onto historic facades during the festival.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mota-production-residency-ljubljana-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:Deadline: MoTA Museum of Transitory Art: Production Residency 2027 
 (Ljubljana)
DESCRIPTION:MoTA (Museum of Transitory Art) in Ljubljana runs an annual ope
 n call for production residencies for media\, sound and visual artists\, c
 urators and researchers. Production residencies offer full support includi
 ng accommodation\, technical support\, production costs and an artist fee\
 ; the exact artist-fee amount is not published on the official or aggregat
 or pages\, so applicants should confirm the figure directly by email. Resi
 dencies run up to one month. Open internationally: artists of all national
 ities and at all professional levels are encouraged to apply\, as individu
 als or collectives. No application fee. The annual deadline is 15 Septembe
 r (for residencies the following year). Apply by email to mota.artists@gma
 il.com with the subject line Application for production residency. Note: t
 he official motamuseum.com SSL certificate is currently expired\, which ma
 y briefly affect link reliability.\n\nOrganisation: MoTA - Museum of Trans
 itory Art\nLocation: Ljubljana\, Slovenia. Open internationally to artists
  of all nationalities and professional levels.\nAward: Full support includ
 ing accommodation\, technical support\, production costs and an artist fee
 . The exact EUR artist-fee amount is not published\; confirm by email. No 
 application fee.\nDuration: Production residency of up to one month.\n\nMo
 re: http://motamuseum.com/RESIDENCY/open-call?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:http://motamuseum.com/RESIDENCY/open-call?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Ljubljana\, Slovenia. Open internationally to artists of all natio
 nalities and professional levels.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:creart-chalet-lecoq-residency-clermont-ferrand-2026@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260621
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260622
SUMMARY:Deadline: CreArt 3.0: Residency at Chalet Lecoq 2026 (Clermont-Ferr
 and)
DESCRIPTION:As part of the CreArt network\, the City of Clermont-Ferrand in
  France is organising a two-month residency for three visual artists at Ch
 alet Lecoq\, selecting two artists from the CreArt network and one from Cl
 ermont-Ferrand. Both central and atypical\, set in the middle of a public 
 garden (the Jardin Lecoq\, a park in the heart of the city)\, the Chalet L
 ecoq is the former janitor's house of the park and invites reflection on t
 he relationship between nature and the urban\, in a place frequented by re
 sidents of all ages. It offers a privileged setting with a two-bedroom apa
 rtment and a fully-equipped workspace\, and welcomes international artists
  in residency throughout the year. An end-of-residency presentation may be
  organised in discussion with the hosted artists. CONDITIONS: residency gr
 ant of EUR 3\,000 per artist (EUR 1\,500/month)\; EUR 600 production costs
  per artist\; for European artists\, reimbursement of round-trip travel up
  to EUR 500\; accommodation and workspace for the two European artists\, a
 nd workspace for the Clermont-Ferrand artist. ELIGIBILITY: artists born or
  resident in one of the following CreArt cities (Kaunas\, Lithuania\; Liep
 aja\, Latvia\; Skopje\, North Macedonia\; Aveiro\, Portugal\; Valladolid\,
  Spain\; Lublin\, Poland\; Venice\, Italy\; Rouen\, France\; Ceske Budejov
 ice\, Czech Republic\; Oulu\, Finland\; Regensburg\, Germany)\; members of
  the Croatian Association of Visual Artists (HDLU)\; and Ukrainian artists
  through cooperation with the Lviv Art Council 'Dialog'. APPLY in English 
 (a single PDF with ID/passport and residency certificate if required\, a o
 ne-page CV\, a portfolio of max 10 pages/10 images\, and a one-page projec
 t proposal) via the CreArt artists' platform. A jury of Clermont-Ferrand c
 ontemporary art professionals selects the artists\, with particular attent
 ion to work that may reveal forms of connection. Deadline: 21 June 2026 (m
 idnight)\; selected candidates announced 3 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Cit
 y of Clermont-Ferrand (CreArt network)\nLocation: Chalet Lecoq\, Jardin Le
 coq\, Clermont-Ferrand\, France.\nAward: Residency grant EUR 3\,000 per ar
 tist for the two-month residency (EUR 1\,500/month)\, plus EUR 600 product
 ion costs per artist. For European (CreArt network) artists: reimbursement
  of round-trip travel up to EUR 500\, and accommodation (a two-bedroom apa
 rtment) plus a fully-equipped workspace\; the Clermont-Ferrand artist rece
 ives the workspace. No application fee.\nDuration: Two-month residency\, 2
 6 October to 20 December 2026\n\nMore: https://creart2-eu.org/open-calls/c
 all-for-applications-residency-at-chalet-lecoq-26-oct-20-dec-2026-clermont
 -ferrand-france?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://creart2-eu.org/open-calls/call-for-applications-residency-at-ch
 alet-lecoq-26-oct-20-dec-2026-clermont-ferrand-france?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Chalet Lecoq\, Jardin Lecoq\, Clermont-Ferrand\, France.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:svetova1-as-we-grow-v-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: SVĚTOVA 1: As We Grow V (Educational & Research Program)
  2026
DESCRIPTION:SVĚTOVA 1 invites early-career artists and cultural organizers
  to apply for the fifth edition of its educational and research programme 
 As We Grow. This year the course is led by artist and mythopoet András Cs
 éfalvay\, Associate Professor at the Academy of Fine Arts in Bratislava. 
 The 14-day project (7 to 20 September 2026) culminates in a group exhibiti
 on. WHAT YOU GET: a free 14-day educational experience\; a scholarship of 
 CZK 5\,000 (around EUR 200)\; a rich working environment with on-site inte
 raction with the leading artist\, scholars and other artists\; active invo
 lvement in the As We Grow research and event programming\; organizational 
 and professional support\; and exhibition of your work at SVĚTOVA 1 for a
 t least six weeks\, with production and PR support before\, during and aft
 er the show. SVĚTOVA 1 actively encourages queer and BIPoC people who hav
 e migrated to or taken refuge in Prague to apply. ELIGIBILITY: applicants 
 must be physically present in Prague for the entire program\, have essenti
 al spoken English\, and commit to the whole 14 days after acceptance. Note
 : accommodation cannot be offered due to funding restrictions. APPLY via t
 he online Notion form with a portfolio of 3 works\, a CV (max 2 pages)\, a
 nd either a 2-3 minute video or a 250-word motivation letter (may include 
 images) outlining how your lived experience and interest align with the co
 urse. Deadline: 30 June 2026 at midnight\; results announced by 15 July 20
 26. Questions: tomas@svetova1.cz.\n\nOrganisation: SVĚTOVA 1\nLocation: P
 rague\, Czech Republic\; participants must be physically present in Prague
  for the entire program.\nAward: Scholarship of CZK 5\,000 (around EUR 200
 ). Free 14-day educational programme\; work exhibited at SVĚTOVA 1 for at
  least six weeks with production and PR support. NO accommodation provided
  (funding restrictions). No application fee.\nDuration: 14 days\, 7 to 20 
 September 2026\n\nMore: https://www.svetova1.cz/project/awg-gravity?utm_so
 urce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.svetova1.cz/project/awg-gravity?utm_source=artificialnouvea
 ugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Prague\, Czech Republic\; participants must be physically present 
 in Prague for the entire program.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:trace-artistic-residencies-memory-displacement-2026-27@artificialnouvea
 u.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260618
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260619
SUMMARY:Deadline: TRACE: Artistic Residencies on Memory\, Displacement & Co
 ntemporary Europe 2026-27
DESCRIPTION:TRACE is an international artistic residency programme\, funded
  by the EU's Creative Europe programme\, exploring how contemporary art ca
 n engage with memory\, war\, displacement\, ecological crisis and the coll
 ective experiences shaping Europe today. It takes as starting points recen
 t and ongoing crises\, including the conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina an
 d the Srebrenica genocide\, Mediterranean migration\, the ecological legac
 y of Chernobyl\, and the Russian invasion of Ukraine\, bringing together a
 rtists\, curators\, researchers and local communities to work with archive
 s\, sites of memory and present-day social realities. WHO THEY SEEK: artis
 ts whose practice engages themes such as memory and remembrance\, identity
 \, war and its consequences\, migration and displacement\, archives and do
 cumentary practices\, the relationship between past and present\, and ecol
 ogical and social transformation\, working across visual arts\, photograph
 y\, film and video\, sound art\, illustration\, graphic storytelling\, pod
 casts and audio\, or interdisciplinary practice. No age restrictions. ELIG
 IBILITY: artists based in countries participating in Creative Europe (EU m
 ember states\; Iceland\, Norway\, Liechtenstein\; and accession/candidate/
 potential-candidate countries including Albania\, Bosnia and Herzegovina\,
  Georgia\, Kosovo\, Montenegro\, North Macedonia\, Serbia\, Ukraine\, Arme
 nia and Tunisia). STRUCTURE: an international jury selects 15 participants
  for three research and workshop programmes (Bosnia and Herzegovina Jul/Au
 g 2026\, Italy Oct 2026\, Ukraine online)\; 6 artists are then selected to
  continue into the 2027 residency programme (on-site in Italy and Bosnia a
 nd Herzegovina\, plus an online residency connected to Ukraine with The 4t
 h Block)\, with outcomes shown in international exhibitions in the partner
  countries (the Ukrainian exhibition in a safe location in Lviv) and the T
 RACE digital archive. WHAT PARTICIPANTS RECEIVE: coverage of travel\, acco
 mmodation and meals during programme activities (up to Creative Europe lim
 its)\, international visibility and PR support\, access to archives and co
 mmunities\, mentorship\, professional documentation and a certificate\; th
 ere is NO daily artist fee and no production equipment. English is the wor
 king language. APPLY via the Google Form with a portfolio (max 5MB PDF) or
  website\, a short project proposal/research idea (max 1 page) and a short
  biography. Deadline: 18 June 2026 (Rome time\, UTC+2)\; selected particip
 ants contacted by 28 June. Questions: info@tracearts.eu.\n\nOrganisation: 
 Camera a Sud (Italy)\, Forgotten Children of War Association (Bosnia and H
 erzegovina) and The 4th Block (Ukraine)\nLocation: Italy\, Bosnia and Herz
 egovina\, and online (Ukraine)\; open to artists based in Creative Europe 
 programme countries.\nAward: NO daily artist fee. Travel\, accommodation a
 nd meals covered during programme activities (up to the maximum allowed un
 der Creative Europe regulations). Technical equipment for producing artwor
 ks is NOT provided. Plus international visibility/PR\, exhibitions\, mento
 rship and a certificate. No application fee.\nDuration: Research missions 
 in 2026 (Bosnia and Herzegovina Jul/Aug\, Italy Oct\, Ukraine online)\; re
 sidencies in 2027 for 6 selected artists\n\nMore: https://docs.google.com/
 forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWVCzfj9fSe_WprayCTcAIucx58JluguVv1dP-x6WlOvCT1Q/viewfor
 m?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWVCzfj9fSe_WprayCTcAIucx58Jl
 uguVv1dP-x6WlOvCT1Q/viewform?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
LOCATION:Italy\, Bosnia and Herzegovina\, and online (Ukraine)\; open to ar
 tists based in Creative Europe programme countries.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:platform-vaasa-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Platform: Residency Program 2027 (Loosey-Goosey)\, Vaasa\
 , Finland
DESCRIPTION:Platform is an art organization in Vaasa\, a relatively periphe
 ral Finnish town\, running an art space and a residency. The 2027 theme\, 
 Loosey-Goosey\, invites working artists to explore the limits of their exp
 ression and question professionalism: what happens to our art when we defi
 ne and limit it to conform to society's lines\, and who decides what makes
  a professional artist. Platform seeks artists who work with the topic of 
 professionalism\, questioning it or rejecting result-driven societal press
 ures and norms. The residency is open to artists of any medium\, including
  but not limited to installation\, performance\, sound art\, textiles\, sc
 ulpture\, video\, community art\, and painting. SUPPORT: a fully funded re
 sidency with a private apartment (bedroom and kitchen) within walking dist
 ance of the dedicated studio and project space\; a working grant of EUR 42
 /day (proportional to days spent in Vaasa)\; a material budget up to EUR 1
 \,000 reimbursed against receipts\; and one return trip (cheapest option) 
 covered. A contact person helps the artist settle in\, source materials an
 d make connections. Platform holds basic tools and electronics (projectors
 \, Zoom recorder\, office printer\, sound system\, sewing machine\, etc.).
  DURATION: 4 to 12 weeks during 2027\; artists who can stay up to 12 weeks
  are preferred\, though 4-8 week requests are considered\, and duos may ap
 ply. EXPECTATIONS: give a public talk\, performance\, workshop or presenta
 tion at the start\; communicate in English\, Swedish or Finnish\; spend at
  least 80 percent of the residency in Vaasa\; and submit project documenta
 tion plus a short report for the website. Platform does not run a gallery\
 , so no end-of-residency exhibition is offered\, but it will help arrange 
 a final presentation\, studio visit or performance if wanted. APPLY: via t
 he online form only\, with a single PDF (max 10 pages\, 5 MB) named FIRSTN
 AME_LASTNAME containing (1) an informal one-page project plan and motivati
 on letter stating preferred 2027 period\, (2) descriptions and images of 5
  previous projects or artworks (direct video links for videos)\, and (3) a
  CV of max two pages including name\, date of birth and current location. 
 Open call: 8 June to 30 June 2026\, 23:59 EEST. All applicants notified by
  the end of September 2026\; the board makes the selection and is not obli
 ged to justify it.\n\nOrganisation: Platform\nLocation: Vaasa\, Finland\; 
 artist must spend at least 80 percent of the residency in Vaasa.\nAward: F
 ully funded. Working grant of EUR 42/day (proportional to days spent in Va
 asa)\, a material budget up to EUR 1\,000 (reimbursed against original rec
 eipts for project-related purchases)\, and travel covered (one return trip
 \, cheapest option). Accommodation provided. No application fee.\nDuration
 : 4 to 12 weeks during 2027 (applicant specifies preferred months)\n\nMore
 : https://platform.fi/residency-program-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://platform.fi/residency-program-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouvea
 ugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Vaasa\, Finland\; artist must spend at least 80 percent of the res
 idency in Vaasa.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:arcathens-athens-residency-fall-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: ARCAthens: Athens Residency Fellowships (Fall 2026)
DESCRIPTION:The Athens Residency is the flagship program of ARCAthens\, a n
 ot-for-profit founded in 2017\, offering two fully-funded Fellowships (Vis
 ual Art and Curatorial) that enable artists\, curators\, and scholars to l
 ive and work in Athens\, Greece\, and respond to the city's ongoing cultur
 al renaissance. The residency is a structured\, research-driven program bu
 ilt around scheduled engagements with artists\, curators\, institutions\, 
 and collections\, including arranged studio and private collection visits\
 , guided institutional access\, and select community events. Distinct from
  studio-isolated models\, it emphasizes engagement and exchange\, balancin
 g focused visits with time for independent exploration. ELIGIBILITY: ARCAt
 hens welcomes applicants from all countries and nationalities representing
  a broad range of creative thought and practice\; the program is open to a
 pplicants not residing in Greece. PRACTICAL: 3-month duration\; USD 3\,000
  Fellowship Prize\; USD 200 per week stipend toward food and local transpo
 rtation\; a basic coach round-trip ticket is provided (Fellows purchase fo
 llowing ARCAthens approval of itinerary and cost\, reimbursed within five 
 business days\; in cases of financial hardship ARCAthens may arrange trave
 l directly). Fellows are responsible for all other expenses\, including fo
 od\, local transportation\, and any production\, installation\, or shippin
 g costs. Visas are not necessary for US nationals for the duration of the 
 program\; others are responsible for procuring visas as applicable. Facili
 ties include a private bedroom and bathroom with shared kitchen\; Visual A
 rt Fellows have studio access. Two Fellows are in residence at one time. W
 orking language is English. Selection is by a 3-person independent committ
 ee of arts professionals. No fee\, open call. TIMELINE: application deadli
 ne 30 June 2026 (closes 11:00 p.m. ET)\; notification of Fellowships mid J
 uly\; residency 10 September to 30 November 2026.\n\nOrganisation: ARCAthe
 ns\nLocation: Athens\, Greece (in-person residency). Open to applicants no
 t residing in Greece\nAward: Fully funded: USD 3\,000 Fellowship Prize\, U
 SD 200/week stipend toward food and local transport\, basic coach round-tr
 ip airfare reimbursed\, private bedroom and bathroom with shared kitchen\,
  and studio access for Visual Art Fellows. No application fee.\nDuration: 
 3 months\, 10 September to 30 November 2026\n\nMore: https://arcathens.org
 /arcathens-athens-residency/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://arcathens.org/arcathens-athens-residency/?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Athens\, Greece (in-person residency). Open to applicants not resi
 ding in Greece
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:emap-emare-media-art-residencies-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261106
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261107
SUMMARY:Deadline: EMAP / EMARE: European Media Art Platform Residencies 202
 7
DESCRIPTION:The European Media Art Platform (EMAP/EMARE) is a network of le
 ading European media-art organisations offering fully funded two-month pro
 duction residencies for artists working with digital media\, including med
 ia art\, bio art and robotic art. Each residency provides a EUR 4\,000 gra
 nt to the applying artist (including subsistence)\, a EUR 4\,000 project b
 udget\, host-provided accommodation\, travel covered according to EU ceili
 ngs\, and access to technical facilities and media labs\; a collaborating 
 artist receives an additional EUR 2\,000 (EUR 6\,000 total for a duo). Res
 idencies take place at one of 15 host institutions across Austria\, France
 \, Slovakia\, Portugal\, Belgium\, the Netherlands\, Slovenia\, Croatia\, 
 Spain\, Italy\, Cyprus\, Greece\, Latvia\, Germany and Poland. ELIGIBILITY
 : applicants must be EU residents or taxpayers in an EU member state\, or 
 residents/taxpayers of one of the eligible non-EU countries (Netherlands-b
 ased artists qualify). Undergraduate and Master's students are not eligibl
 e\; PhD candidates and emerging artists of any age and academic background
  may apply. IMPORTANT: applicants must apply as a duo or collective\, or p
 ropose a collaborative project\, rather than as a purely solo applicant. T
 he 2027 open call runs from 3 September 2026 to 6 November 2026 at 14:00 C
 ET. Apply online at call.emare.eu. No application fee.\n\nOrganisation: Eu
 ropean Media Art Platform (EMAP / EMARE)\nLocation: Two-month production r
 esidency at one of 15 host institutions across Austria\, France\, Slovakia
 \, Portugal\, Belgium\, Netherlands\, Slovenia\, Croatia\, Spain\, Italy\,
  Cyprus\, Greece\, Latvia\, Germany and Poland\nAward: EUR 4\,000 grant fo
 r the applying artist (including subsistence)\; EUR 2\,000 for a collabora
 ting artist (EUR 6\,000 total for a duo)\; EUR 4\,000 project budget\; acc
 ommodation provided by the host\; travel covered per EU ceilings\; access 
 to technical facilities and media labs. No application fee.\nDuration: Two
  months\n\nMore: https://emare.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://emare.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refe
 rral
LOCATION:Two-month production residency at one of 15 host institutions acro
 ss Austria\, France\, Slovakia\, Portugal\, Belgium\, Netherlands\, Sloven
 ia\, Croatia\, Spain\, Italy\, Cyprus\, Greece\, Latvia\, Germany and Pola
 nd
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circus-loops-residency-2026-2028@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCUS LOOPS: European Residency Open Call 2026-2028
DESCRIPTION:CIRCUS LOOPS is a European cooperation project (2026-2028) led 
 by Circusstad Festival (NL)\, Zirkus ON (DE) and Cirkus Kolektiv (HR)\, co
 -funded by the Creative Europe Programme\, inviting contemporary circus ar
 tists and collectives to a residency programme dedicated to developing new
  work through audience engagement. It centres on the Feedback Loops method
 ology\, integrating audience perspectives into the artistic creation proce
 ss. Selected projects take part in three 10-day international residencies 
 in Split\, Karlsruhe and Rotterdam between November 2026 and July 2027 (al
 l projects in residence simultaneously in each location\, working in separ
 ate spaces)\, presenting work-in-progress and engaging in facilitated feed
 back sessions with audiences\, peers and experts. The programme concludes 
 with final presentations at partner festivals between 2027 and 2028. ELIGI
 BILITY: contemporary circus artists and small companies based in Europe (i
 ncluding Creative Europe countries) developing a project at an early or mi
 d stage of creation\; applicants must be available for all residency perio
 ds and commit to the full programme\; teams limited to three core members.
  SUPPORT: a fixed grant of EUR 3\,746 per core team member\, plus travel\,
  accommodation and per diems covered. APPLY via the official online form (
 project description\, artistic team info\, motivation and video material)\
 , in English\, by 17 June 2026\, 23:59 CET. An international jury selects 
 three projects on artistic quality\, motivation\, feasibility and relevanc
 e to the Feedback Loops methodology\; results published by 25 July 2026. C
 ontact: circusloops@gmail.com.\n\nOrganisation: Circusstad Festival (NL)\,
  Zirkus ON (DE) and Cirkus Kolektiv (HR)\, co-funded by Creative Europe\nL
 ocation: Residencies in Split (Croatia)\, Karlsruhe (Germany) and Rotterda
 m (Netherlands)\nAward: Each selected core team member receives a fixed gr
 ant of EUR 3\,746\; travel\, accommodation and per diems are covered by th
 e project partners. No application fee.\nDuration: Three 10-day residencie
 s between November 2026 and July 2027\; final presentations at partner fes
 tivals 2027-2028\n\nMore: https://www.cirkus-kolektiv.org/circus-loops-1?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.cirkus-kolektiv.org/circus-loops-1?utm_source=artificialnou
 veaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Residencies in Split (Croatia)\, Karlsruhe (Germany) and Rotterdam
  (Netherlands)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:decoratelier-workspacebrussels-residency-2026@artificialnouveau.github.
 io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260531
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:Deadline: workspacebrussels: Decoratelier Open Call 2026 (Spatial R
 esearch Residency)
DESCRIPTION:Research-focused residency at Decoratelier in Molenbeek\, organ
 ised through workspacebrussels\, for artists and collectives working with 
 space\, scenography\, installation\, architecture and performative environ
 ments. The residency prioritises research and material experimentation ove
 r production: applicants propose an investigation into spatial practice\, 
 ephemeral architecture or scenographic experimentation connected to the pe
 rforming arts\, engaging directly with the warehouse architecture and reus
 able materials. ELIGIBILITY: artists or collectives based in Belgium or ab
 road. NOTE: this is a context-specific research residency and does not pro
 vide scenographic support for existing productions. Apply via the workspac
 ebrussels Decoratelier open call.\n\nOrganisation: workspacebrussels (resi
 dency at Decoratelier\, Molenbeek)\nLocation: Decoratelier\, Molenbeek\, B
 russels\, Belgium\nAward: EUR 5\,000 budget (incl. VAT) for the residency\
 , plus a 10x18m warehouse hall\, wood and metal workshop access\, reusable
  materials\, junior-builder support three days a week\, artistic and techn
 ical feedback\, a possible internal showing\, and weekday lunch. No applic
 ation fee.\nDuration: Three-week research residency (5 to 23 October 2026)
 \n\nMore: https://www.workspacebrussels.be/en?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.workspacebrussels.be/en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Decoratelier\, Molenbeek\, Brussels\, Belgium
