BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:futures-photography-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260622
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260623
SUMMARY:Deadline: FUTURES Photography: 2027 Residency Open Call
DESCRIPTION:ELIGIBILITY: Open exclusively to current FUTURES artists (exist
 ing members of the FUTURES Photography platform)\; the application is free
  of charge. CONCEPT: The residency supports emerging photographers with ti
 me\, space\, and resources to develop new work\, with a strong emphasis on
  research and artistic process. Artists are invited to explore the interse
 ction of Nature\, Environment\, and Technology - projects should challenge
  perceptions of human and ecological relationships\, technological advance
 ment\, and environmental responsibility. An interdisciplinary approach is 
 encouraged\, and each residency culminates in a public event where artists
  share their work and engage with diverse audiences. LOCATIONS: Three part
 ner venues host residencies at different times in 2027. (1) Futures Hub\, 
 Amsterdam (global FUTURES HQ): a 60 sqm ground-floor studio with heating\,
  electricity\, and private entrance\; live-work space with double folding 
 bed\, private bathroom\, washing machine\, and small kitchen\; sliding doo
 r separates work and living areas\; access to a shared atrium for large-sc
 ale works\, performances\, and presentations\; communal rooftop terrace\; 
 bed linens and towels provided\; available January\, February\, April\, Ma
 y\, June\, September\, October\, November\, December 2027. (2) ISSP\, Riga
 : private bedroom with working space in a shared city-centre apartment wit
 h two other artists\; spacious shared living room and fully equipped kitch
 en\; access to ISSP office facilities including printer\, scanner\, ISSP p
 hotography library\, and studio lights\; available May 2027. (3) Capa Cent
 er\, Budapest: fully furnished private room in a communal apartment at Art
  Quarter Budapest\; 400 sqm shared studio in a postindustrial area\; servi
 ces to integrate residents into the local Budapest art scene and establish
  professional connections\; option to organise a presentation at Capa Cent
 re in downtown Budapest\; access to Capa Centre office facilities (printer
 \, scanner)\; available April 2027. PRESENCE: minimum 90% presence require
 d throughout the residency period. ENGAGEMENT: residents contribute to a V
 isual Diary (one Instagram carousel and two Stories\, in collaboration wit
 h FUTURES)\, a short Video Portrait documenting their process\, a public e
 vent such as an open studio or workshop (open studios on the last Wednesda
 y of the month)\, and a written interview with a local writer published on
  the FUTURES website. FINANCIAL SUPPORT: EUR 1\,000 stipend to cover livin
 g expenses\, materials\, and travel\; accommodation is provided at all loc
 ations. Residents are responsible for arranging travel documents\, health 
 and travel insurance\, liability insurance\, and any visa requirements (su
 pport provided where needed). APPLY: via the FUTURES website\; application
  is free and open only to FUTURES artists. TIMELINE: deadline 22 June 2026
  at 23:59 Amsterdam time\; results announced July 2026. Contact info@futur
 es-photography.com for questions.\n\nOrganisation: FUTURES Photography\nLo
 cation: Futures Hub\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands\; ISSP\, Riga\, Latvia\; Cap
 a Center\, Budapest\, Hungary\nAward: EUR 1\,000 stipend\; accommodation p
 rovided. No application fee.\nDuration: Minimum 1 month\; location-specifi
 c dates in 2027 (Amsterdam: Jan\, Feb\, Apr\, May\, Jun\, Sep\, Oct\, Nov\
 , Dec\; Riga: May\; Budapest: Apr)\n\nMore: https://www.futures-photograph
 y.com/news/futures-residency-open-call-2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.futures-photography.com/news/futures-residency-open-call-20
 27?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Futures Hub\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands\; ISSP\, Riga\, Latvia\; Cap
 a Center\, Budapest\, Hungary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:simone-veil-prize-jewish-cultural-heritage-2026@artificialnouveau.githu
 b.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: Simone Veil Prize for European Jewish Cultural Heritage 2
 026
DESCRIPTION:The Simone Veil Prize\, administered by the European Commission
 \, recognises outstanding projects preserving and promoting European Jewis
 h cultural heritage. It is awarded across five categories: Shared Historie
 s\, Heritage for Dialogue\, Living Heritage\, Cross-border Cooperation and
  Shared Narratives\, and Next Generation/Youth Engagement and Education. A
 WARD: €10\,000 per Grand Prix winner (one per category\, five in total)\
 ; up to 25 finalists receive recognition. ELIGIBILITY: legal or natural pe
 rsons (individuals or organisations) registered in EU Member States or thi
 rd countries associated to the Creative Europe programme\; projects must h
 ave been completed between January 2023 and January 2026. DEADLINE: 31 Jul
 y 2026 at 23:59 CET. APPLY by submitting the completed application form by
  email to applications@simoneveilprize.eu.\n\nOrganisation: European Commi
 ssion\, Directorate-General for Education\, Youth\, Sport and Culture\nLoc
 ation: EU Member States and third countries associated to the Creative Eur
 ope programme\nAward: €10\,000 per Grand Prix winner (five winners\, one
  per category)\; up to 25 finalists recognized. No application fee.\nDurat
 ion: For projects completed between January 2023 and January 2026\n\nMore:
  https://simoneveilprize.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://simoneveilprize.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
LOCATION:EU Member States and third countries associated to the Creative Eu
 rope programme
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vac-belgrade-visual-anthropology-residency@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20271231
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20280101
SUMMARY:Deadline: Visual Anthropology Center (VAC): Residency Programme (Be
 lgrade)
DESCRIPTION:Visual Anthropology Center (VAC) in Belgrade invites filmmakers
 \, visual anthropologists\, artists\, and researchers to apply for its res
 idency programme. The residency specialises in visual anthropology but is 
 also open to individual and collaborative projects in experimental ethnogr
 aphy\, creative documentary film\, and other artistic mediums. Residents m
 ay apply with a project aimed at a public showing\, or use the time and sp
 ace to reflect\, research\, or write without a specific outcome. WHAT IS P
 ROVIDED: accommodation and studio space in central Belgrade\; additional w
 orkspace and community connection through Community Center KROV (an indepe
 ndent creative hub hosting lectures\, events\, and exhibitions)\; project 
 guidance and mentorship from film professionals\, ethnomusicologists\, pro
 ducers\, artists\, curators\, and anthropologists\; connections to local c
 ultural and academic institutions\, archives\, galleries\, and exhibition 
 spaces\; access to camera equipment\, translators for fieldwork or editing
 \, fixers\, and project-specific services or materials\; opportunity to ex
 hibit a final project as an exhibition\, installation\, screening\, worksh
 op\, or lecture. Eligible projects may be promoted through VAC's platforms
  and partner networks\, including the Vizantrop Film Festival\, for region
 al and international visibility. ELIGIBILITY: filmmakers\, visual anthropo
 logists\, artists\, and researchers\; individual and collaborative project
 s welcome. Applications accepted on a rolling basis.\n\nOrganisation: Visu
 al Anthropology Center (VAC)\nLocation: Belgrade\, Serbia (accommodation a
 nd studio in central Belgrade\; additional workspace at Community Center K
 ROV)\nAward: EUR 1\,000–1\,500 per month (stipend\, varies by project re
 quirements)\, plus accommodation and studio space provided. No application
  fee.\nDuration: Approximately 1–2 months\; flexible packages depending 
 on project needs\n\nMore: https://vac.rs/program/residency?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://vac.rs/program/residency?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Belgrade\, Serbia (accommodation and studio in central Belgrade\; 
 additional workspace at Community Center KROV)
END:VEVENT
